{"word":"G1497 - εἴδωλον - eídōlon - i'-do-lon - Idol","slug":"G1497","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">εἴδωλον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>eídōlon"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>i'-do-lon"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Idol"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x03B9;&#x0313;&#x0301;&#x03B4;&#x03C9;&#x03BB;&#x03BF;&#x03BD; - eido&#x0304;lon</b> - <i>i'-do-lon</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G1491\">G1491</a>; an <i>image</i> (that is, for worship); by implication a heathen <i>god</i>, or (plural) the <i>worship</i> of such: - idol."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1493\">G1493</a>, <a href=\"#/G1494\">G1494</a>, <a href=\"#/G1495\">G1495</a>, <a href=\"#/G1496\">G1496</a>, <a href=\"#/G2712\">G2712</a>"}]}